# tests/fixtures/audio/jfk-30s.wav SHA256 anchor.
#
# Placeholder — the actual hash must be written by the owner after running
# the ffmpeg conversion (see README.md "Recipe (owner)" section). The CI
# workflow (.github/workflows/parity-whisper-real.yml) verifies against
# this file with `sha256sum -c`. Until the owner commits both the WAV and
# a real hash line, the workflow's `setup` job detects the absent WAV /
# unusable sidecar and skips the parity leg with an explicit annotation.
#
# Owner recipe:
#   sha256sum tests/fixtures/audio/jfk-30s.wav > tests/fixtures/audio/jfk-30s.wav.sha256
#
# Expected format (one line, two-space-separated, no BOM, no trailing text):
#   <64-hex-chars>  tests/fixtures/audio/jfk-30s.wav
